  "text": "In previous work, the authors have implemented and applied early versions of our algorithms for the coordination of aerial robots in some simple scenarios for area exploration and surveillance missions ( [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). In this paper, we expand and formally present the theoretical results and algorithms that guarantee the synchronization of a team of mobile robots with limited communication range and show how to use our approach in a fault-tolerant cooperative system. Simulations are performed using a group of ARs to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed strategy.",
